# AITBC v0.5.19 Release Notes

**Date**: TBD
**Status**: 🚧 Planned
**Scope**: Tech Debt Cleanup — Cross-Context Import Refactors, Dead Pricing Models, fakeredis

## 🎯 Overview

AITBC v0.5.19 collects the deferred tech debt items from v0.5.13-v0.5.18 that were tagged "future" or "later" but never assigned to a specific release. After verification, 4 of 7 items are already resolved, leaving 3 outstanding items.

**Why this release exists**: During v0.7.4 and v0.8.2 release planning, it was discovered that 7 tech debt items were deferred from v0.5.x to "future" but never tracked. After re-verification (2026-06-29), 4 items were found to be already resolved, leaving 3 outstanding.

**Prerequisites**: [v0.5.18](../v0.5.18/change.log) ✅ (Test Suite Repair). No other prerequisites.

> **Not on the critical path**: No release depends on v0.5.19. These items can be picked up opportunistically.

> **Risk**: Low. All items are code quality or test infrastructure. No consensus, bridge, or trading path is touched.

## 🎯 Release Highlights

### Cross-Context Import Refactor
- 🚧 Refactor certification → reputation cross-context imports (AgentReputation) to service interface/DTO

### Dead Code Cleanup
- 🚧 Wire or remove 6 unused pricing tables (PriceForecast, PricingOptimization, PricingAlert, PricingRule, PricingAuditLog, MarketMetrics duplicate)
- 🚧 Resolve duplicate MarketMetrics and PriceForecast (trading vs marketplace context)

### Test Infrastructure
- 🚧 Add fakeredis for in-process Redis testing (separate deliberate change)
- 🚧 Fix misleading comment in conftest_sqlite.py:57

## 📋 Detailed Features

### Cross-Context Import Refactor (deferred from v0.5.13)

#### Current State — STILL OUTSTANDING
Certification context imports `AgentReputation` directly from reputation context (20 total references):
- `apps/coordinator-api/src/app/contexts/certification/services/certification/badge_system.py:10` — 3 references
- `apps/coordinator-api/src/app/contexts/certification/services/certification/certification_system.py:17` — 6 references
- `apps/coordinator-api/src/app/contexts/certification/services/certification/partnership_manager.py:14` — 11 references

Import pattern: `from ....reputation.services.reputation_service import AgentReputation`

#### Implementation
- Introduce a `ReputationDTO` or `ReputationServiceInterface` in a shared location
- Refactor certification to use the DTO/interface instead of direct model import
- Update all 20 references across 3 files

### Dead Code Cleanup (deferred from v0.5.13)

#### Current State — PARTIALLY ADDRESSED
7 pricing tables in `apps/coordinator-api/src/app/contexts/trading/domain/pricing_models.py`:
- `ProviderPricingStrategy` (line 108) — **PARTIALLY WIRED** (used in `dynamic_pricing.py:344`)
- `MarketMetrics` (line 171) — **DUPLICATE** (also in `marketplace/domain/gpu_marketplace.py:145`)
- `PriceForecast` (line 234) — **DUPLICATE** (also in `marketplace/domain/gpu_marketplace.py:82`)
- `PricingOptimization` (line 287) — **NOT WIRED**
- `PricingAlert` (line 351) — **NOT WIRED**
- `PricingRule` (line 413) — **NOT WIRED**
- `PricingAuditLog` (line 474) — **NOT WIRED** (should be wired — audit trail for pricing changes)

#### Implementation
- Resolve duplicates: decide which context owns MarketMetrics and PriceForecast (trading or marketplace)
- Wire `PricingAuditLog` into dynamic_pricing.py (audit trail for all pricing changes)
- Wire `PricingAlert` and `PricingRule` if useful, or remove if dead code
- Remove `PricingOptimization` if no use case exists
- Add Alembic migration if tables are removed

### Test Infrastructure (deferred from v0.5.18)

